      "content": "That burning sensation is primarily caused by the accumulation of inorganic phosphate and hydrogen ions lowering pH in your muscles, a process often associated with high-intensity efforts like HIIT. Your body gets rid of this metabolite through the Cori cycle, where lactate travels to the liver to be converted back into glucose for reuse. Additionally, active recovery helps clear remaining byproducts through increased blood flow, allowing your muscles to recover within minutes to hours post-workout.",
